{
  "number": 4441,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4441",
  "title": "The documentation for backend search is missing a key information",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nevents.js:62 Uncaught (in promise) Error: Uncaught, unspecified \"error\" event. ([object Object])\r\n    at y.W.emit (events.js:62)\r\n    at te.<anonymous> (InstantSearch.ts:414)\r\n    at te.W.emit (events.js:81)\r\n    at te._dispatchAlgoliaError (algoliasearch.helper.js:1286)\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\nFollow the tutorial, and it gives you the above error\r\nhttps://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/going-further/backend-search/js/\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nSearch done and flowing\r\n\r\n## Found solution\r\n\r\nThe piece of info that is missing from the documentation is the fact that the results from \r\n`index.search` must be enclosed in this way:\r\n```\r\nvar objresult = index.search(\"\", {...});\r\nctx.body = {\r\n  results: [ objresult ]\r\n};\r\n```\r\nIf you provide the result directly from index.search you get the above error.\r\n\r\nHow it was discovered, because the widget showcase and algolia console both have their results enclosed like that.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
